alerts.title:
Lift at Bondi Junction Station not available between the concourse and platforms 1 & 2
Bondi Junction lift to platforms closed for maintenance
alerts.text:
The lift between the concourse and platforms 1 & 2 is temporarily out of service.


From Monday 27 February to Sunday 7 May, the lift between the concourse and platforms at Bondi Junction will be closed for maintenance.


 - For accessible transport between Bondi Junction and the City, catch the 333 bus.

 - For accessible transport between Bondi Junction and Edgecliff, catch the 326, 327 or 328 bus.

 - If you need assistance, speak with station staff, or call 93794843.

 - See the news story for full details.

alerts.title: Blackheath Station upgrade works
alerts.text:
From 26 May 2022 for approximately 12 months, there are upgrade works happening at Blackheath Station.
 
To enable the construction of new accessible lifts, the pedestrian level crossing will be permanently removed from 26 May 2022. During construction, the stairs to the footbridge will be retained to allow cross-corridor access.
 
Customers with mobility or accessibility constraints who are unable to use the footbridge are advised to call 1800 684 490 as soon as possible to arrange
alternate transportation to the nearest accessible station at Katoomba while the pedestrian level crossing is closed.

alerts.title: Buses replace trains between Newcastle Interchange and Morisset
alerts.text:
Wednesday 26 and Thursday 27 April


 - Nightly from 8.45pm to 1.15am, buses replace trains from Newcastle Interchange to Morisset.

 - Buses may leave from stations Newcastle Interchange to Dora Creek up to 45 minutes earlier than the normal train timetable.

 - Some trains from Morisset to Central run to a changed timetable.

 - Nightly from 10.10pm to 3am, buses replace trains from Morisset to Newcastle Interchange.

 - Replacement buses may be impacted by driver shortages. We are doing all we can to minimise the impact to your journey and provide a safe service, however cancellations or delays may occur.

 - Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date real time information. You can also subscribe to planned trackwork alerts.

Bus routes
31CN  Newcastle Interchange, then all stations to Morisset (including Toronto) and return
32CN  Newcastle Interchange, then all stations to Broadmeadow, Cardiff, Toronto, Fassifern, Morisset and return

alerts.title: Buses replace some trains between Wollongong and Kiama
alerts.text:
Wednesday 26 to Friday 28 April
Monday 1 to Friday 5 May
Monday 8 to Friday 12 May


 - Buses replace the following trains between Wollongong and Kiama:


 - 04:40 Central to Kiama

 - 07:45 Kiama to Central

 - 16:52 Bondi Junction to Kiama



 - Replacement buses may be impacted by driver shortages. We are doing all we can to minimise the impact to your journey and provide a safe service, however cancellations or delays may occur.

 - Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date real time information. You can also subscribe to planned trackwork alerts.

Bus routes
5SC Oak Flats, then all stations to Kiama and return (bypassing Bombo in the Oak Flats direction)
